        "text": "The document is an application form for registration as an Independent Market Information System Registered Entity (IMRE) with the Electric Reliability Council of Texas Inc. (ERCOT). It outlines the process for approval in accordance with ERCOT Protocols. Applicants can submit the form electronically and must pay a $500 application fee via Electronic Funds Transfer (EFT) or Automated Clearing House (ACH). The payment should reference the applicant's name and Data Universal Numbering System (DUNS) Number. The form requires the signature of an Authorized Representative or an Officer of the company. ERCOT may request additional information to support operations.\n\nThe form includes sections for:\n\n1. **Entity Information**: \n   - Legal Name and Address of the Applicant\n   - DUNS Number\n\n2. **Authorized Representative (AR)**: \n   - Name, Telephone, and Email Address\n\n3. **Backup Authorized Representative (Optional)**: \n   - Name, Telephone, and Email Address\n\nContact information for assistance is provided, and the document is part of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols effective May 1, 2024.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols/page_2.jpg",
          "page_num": 2,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols",
