    {
      "url": "https://docslib.org/doc/13702242/resource-interconnection-handbook-020116-with-changes-accepted",
      "title": "Resource Interconnection Handbook 020116 with Changes Accepted - DocsLib",
      "text": "Resource Interconnection Handbook 020116 with Changes Accepted - DocsLib\n\n# Resource Interconnection Handbook 020116 with Changes Accepted\n\nTotal Page：16\n\nFile Type：pdf, Size：1020Kb\n\nDownload full-text PDF Read full-text\n\n- Text View\n- Html View\n\nLoad more\n\n54\n\nCopy Link\n\nRESOURCE INTERCONNECTION HANDBOOK\n\nVersion 1.5 01/15/2018\n\nThis handbook is intended to provide a general description of ERCOT’s generator interconnection process for current and potential ERCOT Market Participants. This handbook is not a replacement for the ERCOT Protocols, Operating Guides, Planning Guide, or Other Binding Documents. In the event of any conflict, the ERCOT Protocols, Market Guides, and/or Other Binding Documents (OBDs) shall control. Version Description of Changes Date Author 0.1 Original Document Draft 10/12/2012 Al Garcia 0.2 Editing and reduction of scope 10/24/2012 John Adams 0.3 Editing and Addition of Description of Changes/Table of Contents 10/29/2012 W. Rickerson 0.4 Replacing details of eac",
      "highlights": [
        "handbook is intended to provide a general description of ERCOT’s generator interconnection process for current and  ...    This document provides an overview of the process an Interconnecting Entity or a Resource Entity must follow as it progresses through the Generation Interconnection Process. While this document is primarily written for new Generation  ...    The generation interconnection process has been divided into three stages in this handbook for the purpose of defining the interactions between the developer of the resource and ERCOT. These stages are indicated below.. 1. Interconnection Studies and Project Development\n\n2. Registration and Modeling 3. Energization, Synchronization and Commissioning\n\nFigure 1: Generation Resource Interconnection Process Flow  ...    applicable data and fees. Interconnecting Entities should review section 5.1.1 of the ERCOT Planning Guide for a more  ...    http://www.ercot.com/mktrules/nprotocols/index.html ERCOT Planning Guides Section 5: http://www.ercot.com/mktrules/guides/planning/index Interconnecting Distributed Generation (less than 10 MW and at voltages below 60-kV) is described in PUCT substantive Rule 25.211, and is not discussed in this document. What milestones do I need to keep track of? Figure 2: Major Milestones How long does it take? Every project is different, and study lengths can vary. Interconnecting Entities may apply for interconnection year round, and add their Resource to the list of active projects by submitting a completed GINR application. Provided that all required information is received by ERCOT, interconnection studies are performed in the order in which they are received; however, ERCOT Planning Guides set some timeframes that both ERCOT and Interconnecting Entities must comply  ...    Estimated Duration (days) (from completion of the prior Responsible Result if process process - Some processes Party  ...    Entity documentation is provided. RARF provided to Interconnecting GINR deemed Up to 10 ERCOT Entity incomplete/rejected ERCOT Screening Study Up to 90 ERCOT Decision to proceed to Interconnecting Full Interconnection Up to 180 GINR Cancellation Entity Study (FIS) FIS assigned to a TSP Up to 5 ERCOT ERCOT mediates Interconnecting  ...    ERCOT ERCOT Decision to proceed with and execute Standard Interconnecting Generation Up to 180 GINR Cancellation Entity Interconnection Agreement (SGIA) Submit executed SGIA to Up to 10 TSP ERCOT Review and comment on project’s adherence to Up to 60 days ERCOT binding requirements Resource Registration Up to 180 Resource Entity and Modeling Resource  ...    Checklist Commissioning, requests are rejected Figure 3-Key Process Duration and Deadlines STAGE 1: INTERCONNECTION  ...    Stage 1 of the Generation Interconnection Process is described below in five steps:\n\n1.1.c.1. GINR and Screening Study 1.1.c.2. Full Interconnection Study (FIS)\n\n1.1.c.3. Negotiation of Interconnection Agreement  ...    1. Generation Entity Information Sheet 2. Resource Asset Registration Form RARF) 3. ERCOT Security Screening Study fee  ...    proposed Point of Interconnect (POI). In addition to submitting the GINR application forms, the Interconnecting Entity must pay an ERCOT Security Screening Study fee. The Screening Study fee will be determined by the capacity of the proposed resource. Please refer to the current ERCOT Fee Schedule posted on the ERCOT website for the ERCOT Security Screening Study fee.2 ERCOT may take up to 90 calendar days after submission of the GINR to complete the Screening Study. Details on fee submittal are found in  ...    Upon completion"
