      "text": "ercotZ\n\nCreating an INR fora\nGeneration Resource Under 10 MW\n\nVersion 12.31.21\n\nCreating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW ERCOT Public\nPreface Version 12.31.21  ii\nERCOT RIOO Interconnection Services \nRelease Notes\nDecember 17, 2021\nERCOT has released a new version of Resource Integration and Ongoing Operations -\nInterconnection Services (RIOO - IS) that enables companies to propose a new electricity \ngeneration resource to interconnect to the Texas power grid that ERCOT manages.\nRepresenting the company, an Interconnecting Entity (IE) or Resource Entity (RE) uses the RIOO -\nIS app to create and manage the generation interconnection request (INR) online. The ERCOT \nIntegration Team reviews the INR and conducts studies, along with the Transmission or Distribution \nService Provider who owns the power lines in the area, to understand the effect the resource may \nhave on the grid and determine the economic feasibility of the project.\nAbout this Guide\nThis guide provides informa",
      "highlights": [
        "ERCOT RIOO Interconnection Services \nRelease Notes\nDecember 17, 2021 ERCOT has released a new version of Resource Integration and Ongoing Operations - Interconnection Services (RIOO - IS) that enables companies to propose a new electricity  ...    IS app to create and manage the generation interconnection request (INR) online. The ERCOT  ...    have on the grid and determine the economic feasibility of the project.\nAbout this Guide This guide provides information about performing the tasks in RIOO - IS to create and submit the  ...    Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW ERCOT Public\nPreface Version 12.31.21  iii\nDelayed Features • The online payment system for small distributed generation resource projects is postponed. You must pay your application fee by one of the following methods: • The Compliance With The Lone Star Infrastructure Protection Act Attestation regarding  ...    Supporting Documentation\nRIOO Services documentation available from the Resource Integration page of the ercot.com website:\n• IE Sign Up Guide for RIOO Services\n• RE Sign Up Guide for RIOO Services  ...    • Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW\n• Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Over 10MW • Managing Your INR as an IE/RE\n• Managing INRs as a TSP/DSP Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW ERCOT Public\nPreface Version 12.31.21  iv\nTable of Contents Understanding the INR Process..................................................................................................... 1 Before Starting Your INR............................................................................................................... 2 Sign Up for a RIOO Services User Account  ...    Have Documents Available to Attach and Upload........................................................................ 2 Check for Electronic Payment Debit Blocks................................................................................. 3 Starting Your INR Project  ...    Providing the Basic INR  ...    Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW ERCOT Public\nUnderstanding the INR Process Version 12.31.21  1 Understanding the INR Process The online INR application starts with setting the size of the resource as small or large and if it will be transmission or distribution connected to the grid, and then identifying the fuel and technology powering the resource, the megawatts it will be injecting into and withdrawing from the grid, and the estimated time frame when it available to the grid market operations. You must upload and attach  ...    After identifying the resource location (Texas county, latitude and longitude coordinates, and  ...    submitting and make edits as necessary before you electronically sign and submit the INR. As you finish entering information on a page, clicking the Continue button saves the information  ...    As you supply information and make selections about the resource, you can track your progress  ...    application process later. After you electronically submit your INR and send in your fee payment, ERCOT has 10 days to review it for technical accuracy. ERCOT may start corresponding with you about modifications to various entries before the request is considered accepted. Each time ERCOT sends questions or concerns, an alert will display in your INR List along with the action to view it and respond. When the INR application is deemed complete, ERCOT will send you  ...    Creating an INR for a Generation Resource Under 10MW ERCOT Public\nBefore Starting Your INR Version 12.31.21  3  ...    Click 1 up to 9.99 MW.\nClick Let’s Go.\nClick Distribution Connected.\nRE ONLY: Click the name of the company  ...    Providing the Basic INR Information Version 12.31.21  9\nEstimate Your Energization, Synchronization, and Commercial Operations Date \nClick Continue.\nThe Energization Date estimates when the resource facility’s equipment  ...    Reminder: This date must be coordinated with the TSP’s PLD for"
