reach out to ERCOT at least 30 days prior to the deadline for their  ...    data.\nPUBLIC\nStage 3: Resource Commissioning Milestones\n12\nSubmit \nCommissioning \nPlan\nPart 1: \nEnergization\nPart 2: Synchronization\nPart 3: Full \nCommissioning\nPUBLIC\nSTAGE 3: Energization, Synchronization and Commissioning \n13  ...    The three-part ERCOT New Generator Commissioning Checklist is designed to coordinate the energization,  ...    • Part 2: Request for Initial Synchronization (up to 20 MVA, > 20 MVA)\n• IRR Curtailment Test • Reactive Power Capability Test\n• Voltage Support Service (VSS) Test (Calculated)  ...    • Resources requesting commercial operation outside of the Summer and Winter seasons do not need to submit a declaration of weather preparedness for Part 3 Approval. • Those new resources can be declared together with other existing resources during the May 1 – Jun 1 and  ...    Generator has now completed the interconnection process.\nPUBLIC\nSmall Generation Process\n14 The Small Generation process is governed by Planning Guide Section 5.4.  ...    • System Impact Study – Conducted by TDSP (Operating Guide Section 2.9 [VRT], Operating Guide Section 2.6 and 2.9 [FRT and VRT] and Planning Guide Section 5.4.2)\n• Resource Data Submission – Entered into RIOO by IE/RE  ...    PUBLIC\nResource Integration page\n15\nPUBLIC\nResource Interconnection Handbook\n16\nGeneration Interconnection Requests\n17 1,881 active generation interconnection requests totaling 372 GW as of September 30th, 2024 (Solar 154 GW, Wind 35 GW, Gas 26 GW, and Battery 154 GW) (Excludes capacity associated with projects designated as Inactive per Planning Guide Section 5.7.6) Generation Interconnection Requests\nSmall Gen"
